Package jakarta.validation.metadata

Enum MethodType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<MethodType>
      • jakarta.validation.metadata.MethodType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<MethodType>
    public enum MethodType
extends java.lang.Enum<MethodType>
    Represents the type of a method: getter or non getter.
    Since:
    1.1
    Author:
    Emmanuel Bernard

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • GETTER

        public static final MethodType GETTER
        A method following the getter pattern. A getter according to the JavaBeans specification is a method whose:
        • name starts with get, has a return type but no parameter
        • name starts with is, has a return type and is returning boolean.

      • NON_GETTER

        public static final MethodType NON_GETTER
        A method that does not follow the getter pattern. A getter according to the JavaBeans specification is a method whose:
        • name starts with get, has a return type but no parameter
        • name starts with is, has a return type and is returning boolean.

      • valueOf

        public static MethodType valueOf​(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the enum constant of this type with the specified name. The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an enum constant in this type. (Extraneous whitespace characters are not permitted.)
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
        Returns:
        the enum constant with the specified name
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if this enum type has no constant with the specified name
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the argument is null
